#: src/gui-gtk4/uifiles/siril_stacking.ui:313
msgid ""
"Seven rejection algorithms are available:\n"
"\n"
"<b>Percentile Clipping</b> is a one-step rejection algorithm ideal for small "
"sets of data (up to 6 images).\n"
"\n"
"<b>Sigma Clipping</b> is an iterative algorithm which will reject pixels "
"whose distance from median will be farthest than two given values in sigma "
"units.\n"
"\n"
"<b>MAD Clipping</b> is an iterative algorithm working as Sigma Clipping "
"except that the estimator used is the Median Absolute Deviation (MAD). This "
"is generally used for noisy infrared image processing.\n"
"\n"
"<b>Median Sigma Clipping</b> is the same algorithm except than the rejected "
"pixels are replaced by the median value.\n"
"\n"
"<b>Winsorized Sigma Clipping</b> is very similar to Sigma Clipping method "
"but it uses an algorithm based on Huber's work [1] [2].\n"
"\n"
"<b>Linear Fit Clipping</b> is an algorithm developed by Juan Conejero, main "
"developer of PixInsight [2]. It fits the best straight line (y=ax+b) of the "
"pixel stack and rejects outliers. This algorithm performs very well with "
"large stack and images containing sky gradients with differing spatial "
"distributions and orientations.\n"
"\n"
"The <b>Generalized Extreme Studentized Deviate Test</b> algorithm [3] is a "
"generalization of Grubbs Test that is used to detect one or more outliers in "
"a univariate data set that follows an approximately normal distribution. "
"This algorithm shows excellent performances with large dataset of more 50 "
"images.\n"
"\n"
"[1] Peter J. Huber and E. Ronchetti (2009), Robust Statistics, 2nd Ed., "
"Wiley\n"
"[2] Juan Conejero, ImageIntegration, Pixinsight Tutorial\n"
"[3] Rosner, Bernard (May 1983), Percentage Points for a Generalized ESD Many-"
"Outlier Procedure, Technometrics, 25(2), pp. 165-172"
msgstr ""
"7 種類の外れ値除去アルゴリズム が利用できます.\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Percentile Clipping</b> は 1 回の処理で外れ値を除去するシンプルな方法。"
"画像が 6 枚程度までの小規模スタックに最適です。.\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Sigma Clipping</b> は反復アルゴリズムで、中央値からの距離が、指定された "
"2 つのシグマ値より大きいピクセルを除外します。\n"
"\n"
"- <b>MAD Clipping</b> Sigma Clipping と同様の反復処理ですが、推定量として "
"Median Absolute Deviation（MAD）を使用します。ノイズの多い 赤外線画像 でよく"
"使われます。\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Median Sigma Clipping</b> Sigma Clipping と同じ手法ですが、除外されたピ"
"クセルを中央値で置き換える点が異なります。\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Winsorized Sigma Clipping</b> Sigma Clipping に非常に似ていますが、"
"Huber の研究 [1][2] に基づくアルゴリズムを使用します。\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Linear Fit Clipping</b> PixInsight の主要開発者である Juan Conejero に"
"よって開発されたアルゴリズムです [2]。ピクセルスタックに最も適合する直線"
"（y=ax+b）をフィットし、外れ値を除外します。このアルゴリズムは、大きなスタッ"
"クや空の勾配が異なる空間分布や方向を持つ画像で非常に良好に動作します。\n"
"\n"
"- <b>Generalized Extreme Studentized Deviate Test</b> [3] Grubbs 検定を一般化"
"した外れ値検出法で、ほぼ正規分布に従うデータから複数の外れ値を検出できます。"
"50 枚以上の大規模データセットで非常に高い性能を発揮します。\n"
"\n"
"[1] Peter J. Huber and E. Ronchetti (2009), Robust Statistics, 2nd Ed., "
"Wiley\n"
"[2] Juan Conejero, ImageIntegration, Pixinsight Tutorial\n"
"[3] Rosner, Bernard (May 1983), Percentage Points for a Generalized ESD Many-"
"Outlier Procedure, Technometrics, 25(2), pp. 165-172"

